        section#descricao.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center
                    h1 Tourism

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead.fw-bold The diploma of higher professional technician in Tourism is awarded to students who demonstrate, in this area:
                    p.lead a) develop and deepen the knowledge acquired;
                    p.lead b) apply the knowledge acquired, in order to show a professional approach to the work developed;
                    p.lead c) solve problems and construct and substantiate their own arguments;
                    p.lead d) collecting, selecting and interpreting the relevant information, which enables the support of the recommended solutions and the judgments issued, including in the analysis the relevant social, scientific and ethical aspects;
                    p.lead e) communicate information, ideas, problems and solutions to both specialist and non-specialist audiences;
                    p.lead f) develop skills that enable lifelong learning with a high degree of autonomy.

       
        section#req.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Access Requirements

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead Students who obtain a minimum grade of 95 points (on a scale of 0 to 200) in one of the following national entrance exams can apply: Geography (09) or History (11) or Portuguese (18)


        section#perfil.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Profile of the study program

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead The profile of the study program comprises the development of technical-scientific knowledge and knowledge of a professional nature in the areas of Tourism studies.

        section#diplomados.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Occupational profile of graduates

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead The degree in Tourism is part of the training area of Tourism, Sports and Leisure, and its graduates are qualified to carry out a professional activity, within the scope of the profile of the study program.

